text: St. Cross College is one of the colleges of the University of Oxford. It is a graduate college only. It does not have any undergraduate students. The College was founded in 1965. It was named after St. Cross Road, where the college's first buildings were located. In 1981 it moved to its current location on St. Giles Road. ==References== Category:1965 establishments in England Category:Colleges of the University of Oxford
title: St Cross College, Oxford
